  I think the idea is to get back on the road to get the bus to the show and
then home to do it right. The crank and flywheel are more then likely junk
now anyway and they can complete their journey, have a good time and make
permanent repairs when they do get home. I drove 500 miles leaking massive
amounts of oil in order to make the shows I was heading to, finally had to
park the bus and hitch a ride home and that was only because the clutch was
slipping to much to make it any further. Bussing is about doing it, road
side quick fixes, etc. At least that is the way I feel about bus driving.

ronnie

